Potential vulnerability: integer overflow when casting arg to unsigned int? arg is unsigned long; they compare (unsigned int)arg >= cdi->capacity. If sizeof(unsigned long) > sizeof(unsigned int) (e.g., 64-bit), high bits truncated, could allow large arg to wrap to small value, bypass check, leading to out-of-bounds access. That's a classic issue. So similar to CVE-2013-4588? That CVE deals with ioctl command validation and length. Here we have insufficient validation of arg size, possible out-of-bounds read of info->slots. That's a memory read, not write, but still vulnerability.

